        "text": "; cf., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 15:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The original train of thought was, \"I will not keep silence, for I shall first of all keep silence when,\" etc. Instead of ‛al chēqâm, \"Upon their bosom,\" we might have 'el chēqâm, into their bosom, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
